mit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMy/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-and-elevation-885832-885832.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMy/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-and-elevation-885832-885832.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMy/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-and-elevation-885832-885832.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMy/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-and-elevation-885832-885832.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMy/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-and-elevation-885832-885832.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMy/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-and-elevation-885832-885832.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMy/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-and-elevation-885832-885832.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"the-price-changes-make-the-sierra-ev-significantly-more-affordable-than-the-tesla-cybertruck\"\u003eThe price changes make the Sierra EV significantly more affordable than the Tesla Cybertruck\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eIncluding the $2,095 destination charge, the new Sierra EV now starts at just $64,495, which gets you into the Elevation trim. If that wasn\u0026#39;t enough, the luxurious Denali trim level is now available with a Standard Range battery, which drops the Denali\u0026#39;s start price to $71,795. Perhaps most remarkably, even the aggressive GMC Sierra EV AT4 undercuts the infamous \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/tesla/\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eTesla\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/reviews/tesla-cybertruck-first-look-interior-exterior-review\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eCybertruck\u003c/a\u003e. After destination fees, the Cybertruck starts at $82,235—a precious $840 more than the AT4\u0026#39;s starting price of $81,395. Take a minute to do the math for the other trim levels, and you\u0026#39;ll find the standard Sierra EV comes in at $17,740 cheaper than the Cybertruck, while the feature-packed Denali saves you $10,440 compared to a Cybertruck.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg1ODMw/2026-gmc-sierra-ev-at4-885830.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eThe Sierra EV is a lot more competitive than it was last year, and its incredible price point makes it a bit of a no-brainer for people genuinely trying to decide between the Cybertruck and another option. But GM still has competition in the electric truck segment, most notably from \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/ford/\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eFord\u003c/a\u003e\u0026#39;s F-150 Lightning XLT, which starts at an extremely close $65,190 for 2025. Like GMC, Ford has brought a careful selection of new features to the Lightning, in what promises to be quite a difficult duo to cross shop. Either way, the GMC Sierra EV badly needed an entry point below $90,000, and thankfully, it\u0026#39;s finally here.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2025 Dodge Charger Daytona\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(min-width: 790px) 375px, (min-width: 768px) calc(50vw - 80px), calc(100vw - 24px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com